cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.GT

This paper deals with the deployment of small cells in 5G networks to reduce latency and increase radio access capacity, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of mobile edge computing technology to manage dedicated cache space in the radio access network also involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and information theory (cs.IT). The study of a competitive caching scheme among content providers can be seen as a game theory problem (cs.GT), while the optimization of caching policies based on popularity and availability of contents can be considered as a problem in social networks (cs.SI).
